      • sortMatrixRowsWithProteinDataRowsFirst

        public void sortMatrixRowsWithProteinDataRowsFirst()
        Sorts matrix rows so that rows that contain protein data have the lowest index. Example: Row 0 (no protein data), Row 1 (protein data), Row 2 (protein data), Row 3 (no protein data) is sorted to: Row 2, Row 1, Row 0, Row 3.
